          "rationale": "Workers' compensation is elective for private Texas employers, but a venue that chooses not to carry coverage (a non-subscriber) with non-exempt employees must file the DWC Form-005 non-subscriber notice - within 30 days of its first hire and again each year between February 1 and April 30 (Tex. Labor Code 406.004; the annual window is stated on the form). Separately, EVERY employer - subscriber or not - owes the 406.005 employee coverage-notice duty, tracked as its own obligation.",
